    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n8808" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τέρας</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ατος</span> and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αος</span> (cf.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τεῖρος, ἀστήρ</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">prodigy,
            portent, omen</span>, found in some manifestation of nature, such
          as thunder, lightning, the rainbow. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τέρας
            Διός</span>, ‘sent by Zeus,’ <i><span class="en">Il.
            12.209</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἀνθρώπων</span>, ‘for men,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 11.28</span></i>; of a <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">monster</span>,
          the Gorgon, <i><span class="en">Il. 5.742</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
